Nagakute, 1584 (?) Tactically, it was a victory for
the Tokugawa, as they destroyed the force that was
sent under Ikeda Shonyu around their lines.
Strategically, it was a draw, as both Ieyasu and
Hideyoshi realized they had much more to gain by
working together than by fighting each other. 

Nate
